tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE vocal_exercises (
    exercise_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    exercise_name VARCHAR(255),
    difficulty_level INT,
    duration_minutes INT,
    target_vocal_range VARCHAR(50),
    recommended_tempo INT,
    instructions TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE singer_profiles (
    singer_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    singer_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    voice_type VARCHAR(50),
    vocal_range VARCHAR(50),
    preferred_exercise_id UUID REFERENCES vocal_exercises(exercise_id)
);

CREATE TABLE exercise_ratings (
    rating_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    exercise_id INT NOT NULL,
    singer_id INT NOT NULL,
    rating INT,
    review TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE Singer_Exercises (
	singer_id INT,
	exercise_id INT,
	completed_date DATE,
	PRIMARY KEY (singer_id, exercise_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (singer_id) REFERENCES Singers(id),
	FOREIGN KEY (exercise_id) REFERENCES Exercises(id)
);
